Use this README file to introduce your application and point to useful places in the API for learning more.
Run "rake doc:app" to generate API documentation for your models, controllers, helpers, and libraries.

!! Gems

Inherited Resources
   Base class for controllers to inherit all restful actions
   https://github.com/josevalim/inherited_resources
   gem install inherited_resources

Liquid
  Safe, customer facing template language for flexible web apps
  https://github.com/tobi/liquid
  gem install liquid


!! Internationalization and Localization

We use these languages:
  <ul>
  <li>DE: Deutsch a.k.a. German
  <li>EN: English
  <li>ES: Espanol a.k.a. Spanish
  <li>FR: French
  <li>HI: Hindi
  <li>IT: Italian
  <li>JA: Japanese
  <li>ZH: Chinese
  </ul>

We use these naming conventions for strings:
  <ul>
  <li>name_in_de: Name in Deutsh a.k.a. German
  <li>name_in_en: Name in English
  <li>name_in_es: Name in Espanol a.k.a. Spanish
  <li>etc.
  </ul>

We use these currencies:
  <ul>
  <li>CHF: Swiss Franc
  <li>CNY: China Yuan
  <li>EUR: Euro
  <li>GBP: Great Britain Pound
  <li>INR: India Rupee
  <li>JPY: Japan Yen
  <li>USD: United States Dollar
  </ul>

We use these naming conventions for prices:
  <ul>
  <li>price_in_chf: Price in Swiss Francs
  <li>price_in_cny: Price in China Yuans
  <li>price_in_eur: Price in Euros
  <li>etc.
  </ul>


!! Resources

Users
  username:string
  password:string
  name_in_en:string
  description_in_en:string

Shops
 name_in_en:string
 description_in_en:string

Shopkeepers
  user_id:integer
  shop_id:integer

Items
 name_in_en:string
 length:decimal
 width:decimal
 height:decimal
 mass:decimal
 price_in_usd:decimal
 shop_id:integer

Images
  name_in_en:string
  width:integer
  height:integer
  src:string
  longdesc:string
  path:string

